data.title: Long wait for NOT REAL MEAT
data.text: Went in on 6-19-2016 waited 20 minutes because only one person worked there, Did you know that this is not even real meat. Their chicken looked like a giant  un-fried chicken nugget. Never going to eat Subway again.

data.title: Subway, on Main Street, El Cajon,  CA
data.text: I always enjoy a sub sandwich from here, the people are friendly and courteous.  Toasting the sandwich really adds flavor. You get good value and a very sandwich for the price, especially on the daily special.

data.title: Best Subway in San Diego
data.text: You are greeted with a "welcome" as you enter the door. The girls that wait on you are friendly and gracious with so many choices for your sandwich. the ingredients are fresh and made exactly as you want it. The price is always right, with specials very often. The store is clean and neat and big enough for most customers who want to sit and eat lunch.

data.title: What a deal!
data.text: Always fresh and healthy if you make the right choices.  It's a great weeknight treat when you don't feel like cooking and just want to sit in front of the tv and munch on something tasty.  Sure, there are more exciting meals but my husband and I share a foot long and a couple of cookies and we're satisfied without feeling stuffed.

data.title: inexpensive sandwiches
data.text: Good and Filling inexpensive sandwiches.  Good if you are on the go, and in a hurry, pick one up and eat while on the road...

data.title: bons sanduiches
data.text: O Subway tem bons sanduiches, é gostoso e saudavel, com grande variedade de opções de recheios e pães gostosos.

data.title: O mesmo (ainda bem!)
data.text: Nossa visita ao Subway foi satisfatória, pois o lanche não era diferente do que conhecíamos, e estava gostoso, a um bom preço. Infelizmente as atendentes não estavam com muita vontade de sorrir, mas... valeu pelo lanche!
